==Old English==
===Spellings===
-ung, -ing

===Etymology===
From Germanic: cognate with Old Saxon [[-unga]] (Dutch [[-ing]]), Old High German [[-unga]] (German ''-ung''), Old Norse ''-ung'', [[-ing]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ʊŋg/

===Suffix===
'''-ung'''
# forming [[nouns]] from [[verbs]], denoting verbal action or an instance of it; or denoting a substance involved in the verbal action

